The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning model for traffic light cycle control, which involves collecting traffic data and dividing the intersection into small grids. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the model involves optimizing the traffic light duration based on real-time traffic information, which suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper employs a convolutional neural network to map states to rewards, indicating that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
